[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating git setup dependencies**\n\nI need to consider whether to check existing metadata and if the setup includes the git executable. While tests can construct command lines, they don't execute them, and normal usage requires an external git CLI to be installed. The local TCK Ubuntu likely has git, but for deterministic setups, I need to figure out if I can install git outside of Docker. If meaningful coverage through real SCM execution is needed, it seems essential to ensure that git is installed.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ebf27141d61ba6b016a2a4317afa88190bcf7a14890f89343\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKkMeoP5jqFyOqrBZD-2xZUOPmX1aEPbMgj1gNUzLpse-VFnRXrd5FLaXBmqk9rYIg5lbxOzzQngJlHdLCQ4vFgtZEhQ2doULqDflzW0pmRzHm18Y8uN-On2cC0fcn6wTD-36VzOMHhvdP13GU0-Xl3yXb6RmZc4f9UQMl0tE0m1J3L1JjjgY623ipZmOyDaClCfW0XwqrUK8ZN8Cf9vEiz3XQSZPQZEyWk3qQHRjO2pDuyflx9GUdbqVMwSRB1UbnjdhVSMS-Gq43Kxp7wo4U7iVWcm22ifBrDxe93-aJBgQpfz1JKbK93jFuPQHFKooZMnOh5eiYWV67mAlret7nm02PwztkT3EUfhTMcHY5YalbXpiiKqJD4Ty7GMiqDSzeHaQiEDs6NsMQ8CnU31LI30EOaznhorgooP-aZJ5rEGwbmQ0b-7RAw6XpDQUFYSqNdhh9J9DnkCrQaFd157bd4mtKiPqRwEmq-JnUDW_iJgt7tajWhM97jjGtIEOrXCk8WX9PdfyfFY5ClyOBhOmdjlws0r3D4vY0h2Wq8OsFbCoUamEdjEsIHhVQmdNIb2Ah4XWH6UKaJvK4npASFaGxBsqwjbzJkgE2J_zBkJGjszPRZ9KcxHcAOlre27kgpmIBUkUBiS5qaMDkOhfwAy91WvHEmJ8Z0MxWRSvabdkSp9G_1BXlBPwat9BbBYIaC-TXW5r2EWVkt4KoBgeHTV8VO0SNPsIjLs9jxIMFZh2fqF3LpAYWu3WTnXfsDNuLMNqQfMawKx3wjiO1P7ST_CHjKBKg0UJw_hZOpoZYfZqJqWz4ATrLMzFwF5QfFGGaN-TPfrzvwxr__R9TkSvxDqOQzyNKf8N35gNoqXfSEBO-ETCMGIQnmhj5njMgFGrVXAgrEElQnAJL-6kpYXuSFWoYFcwkupf-bapvW8RpKAsE4-H2wUtD8cpWHHCnWRbkqRHnzCKiczD8c7aQFqNfY8HZ4PIfWBnYxQtkuNcSBpd6V-mkZSUf_dI8QDFmEbvi1j1ewCgx-HqnLamev6adk33iohQ_X2bX9a3k2O8TDFOOR_HBBpqkLBFF1Vtti4_r_QTOOdq6dqRUIYhub_J_X4ptTC-XjbeXEhesP0dWZnWUxYbggZFetX4ggpVIApO-JqVZQrrqMqHWJQiw8U-mGlfSQuimcT5S6d2DuZ1KbsF2CwoSizSuNX9JPHfNyowu0anBnJR62