m properties in the guidance. I’ve found that upstream tests call setDefaultGitConfig before running commit or tag tests, so I need to decide whether to include that detail.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed; the artifact's runtime dependencies are transitive and it is a Git CLI provider. Meaningful command-execution coverage does need test-code setup of a temporary local Git repository.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For tests that execute real provider commands, create a temporary local Git repository, run `git init`, and configure repository-local `user.name` and `user.email` before commits or tags. Prefer local file/URI repositories and parser/command-line coverage; avoid network, SSH, GPG signing, and global Git configuration. For 2.2.1, adapt tag/signing tests to the `SignOption` API and instance `createPushCommandLine` where needed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The provider relies on the external `git` executable; Ubuntu runners normally have it, but local Gradle/native-image verification is authoritative.\",\n    \"Signed tag or signed commit paths require GPG/key setup and should be avoided unless deliberately testing signing.\",\n    \"SSH remote tests would require key and host-key handling; avoid them for deterministic coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ebf27141d61ba6b016a2a4372c0888190a2361d7e4d53df77\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2353, "output": 1291, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45116, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781154649821, "responseId": "resp_0ebf27141d61ba6b016a2a435a4b708190a5bad6f9ee405617"}}
